# Demo data context

Low-level `list_*` helpers in `phase2_modules_service.py` require keyword-only `demo=`. Call them only from the page data layer or with demo passed explicitly from the caller.

## Good pattern

Page / component owns context; services receive rows or demo from above:

```python
# app/pages/_core/_data.py — demo wired once, cached
rows, used = list_inventory(demo=list(_DEMO_INVENTORY))

def load_inventory() -> list[dict[str, Any]]:
    rows, used = _cached_inventory_rows()
    return list(rows)
```

```python
# Component — use load_* from page data, pass rows down
inventory_rows = load_inventory()
image_context = build_catalog_image_context(
    assets_by_id=assets_by_id,
    inventory_rows=inventory_rows,
)
```

## Avoid

- `list_inventory()` with no `demo=` — raises `TypeError`
- Deep services importing `_DEMO_INVENTORY` or calling `get_inventory()` when the page already has `load_inventory()`
- Components reaching into `phase2_modules_service.list_*` directly

## Layering

| Layer | Responsibility |
|-------|----------------|
| `_core/_data.py` | `load_inventory()`, `load_assets()`, … — attach `demo=`, cache, mark demo mode |
| Components / pages | Call `load_*`; pass row lists into services and UI helpers |
| Services | Accept preloaded rows; optional fallback to `load_*` only when no caller context |

When adding a new `list_*` consumer, thread data from the page the same way `load_assets()` is already passed into `render_hand_tools_tab(all_assets=…)`.
